      "description": "Offered is an exceptional E46 M3, a paragon of mechanical integrity and Bavarian engineering. Powered by the S54B32 power plant, this unit features a high-compression 8,000 RPM redline, individual throttle bodies, and a meticulously calibrated double-VANOS system for optimal volumetric efficiency across the rev range. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission and a 3.62:1 M-variable limited-slip differential, ensuring precise power delivery. This example boasts a documented reinforced rear subframe and a suspension geometry maintained to factory tolerances with upgraded bushings and dampers. The chassis remains rigid and communicative, showing zero signs of thermal or structural fatigue. With a comprehensive service dossier including recent rod bearing prophylaxis and valve adjustments, this vehicle is a definitive specimen for the discerning purist seeking a concours-level driving experience.",
